features.technical_notes:
The V1 scope must remain as a nested registration for hook isolation — auth, rate-limit, security hooks are added to v1Scope, not to the /api scope. Admin plugins have their own onRequest auth hooks so they don't need V1 scope hooks. New structure:
await server.register(async (apiScope) => {
  await apiScope.register(async (v1Scope) => { /* hooks + routes */ }); // no prefix
  await apiScope.register(adminKeysPlugin);
  await apiScope.register(adminAuditPlugin);
  await apiScope.register(adminConfigPlugin);
}, { prefix: "/api" });
